Introduction

This is the script of making figure 3a-c & supplementary figure 1d including: heatmaps showing correlation bwtween basic phenotypes and phenotypes Scatter plots shown in the manuscript

library(ggplot2)

Correlation between basic phenotypes and immune cell proportion:

dat<-read.table("~/Documents/working/projects/300DM/Age_gender_seasonal_effect/DM5P_GPenPCalc_Percent_matchedRtHversion.txt",header=T,row.names=1,sep="\t",check.names = F)
####242 277

##remove cytokine with >20% NA
clean_data_number<-apply(dat,2,function(w) {tmp<-na.omit(w);length(tmp)})
keep<-which(clean_data_number>=0.2*nrow(dat))
clean_data<-dat[,keep]           
####242 301

##remove samples with NA
clean_data2<-na.omit(clean_data)
####242 301
clean_data2<-clean_data2[,1:149]
####
phe<-read.table("~/Documents/working/projects/300DM/Age_gender_seasonal_effect/phe_300DM.txt",header=T,row.names = 1)
names(phe)<-c("Days_from_Jan_16","Sin","Cos","Gender","Age")
ol<-intersect(rownames(clean_data2),rownames(phe))
clean_data3<-clean_data2[ol,]
phe<-phe[ol,]

####SPEARMAN
res<-matrix(nrow=ncol(clean_data3),ncol=ncol(phe))
res<-as.data.frame(res)
names(res)<-names(phe)
rownames(res)<-names(clean_data3)

###coefficients
cor<-matrix(nrow=ncol(clean_data3),ncol=ncol(phe))
cor<-as.data.frame(cor)
names(cor)<-names(phe)
rownames(cor)<-names(clean_data3)
###

for (cyto in rownames(res)){
  for (co in names(res)){
    t <-cor.test(clean_data3[,cyto],phe[,co],method = "spearman") 
    res[cyto,co]<-t$p.value
    cor[cyto,co]<-t$estimate[[1]]
  }
}

##fdr
res<-as.matrix(res)
p_vals<-as.numeric(res)
fdr<-p.adjust(p_vals,method = "fdr")
fdr_matrix<-matrix(fdr,nrow=nrow(res),ncol=ncol(res))
fdr<-as.data.frame(fdr_matrix)
rownames(fdr)<-rownames(cor)
names(fdr)<-names(cor)

####
anno<-read.table("~/Documents/working/projects/300DM/Age_gender_seasonal_effect/anno.txt",header=T,row.names = 1,sep="\t",check.names = F)
sam<-as.character(rownames(cor))
name1<-anno[sam,]
rownames(cor)<-name1$name
rownames(fdr)<-name1$name
rownames(anno)<-anno$name
anno<-anno[,c(3,4,6)]
anno<-anno[rownames(cor),]
cor<-cbind(cor,anno)
cor_value<-c(cor$Gender,cor$Age,cor$Days_from_Jan_16,cor$Sin,cor$Cos)
Subpopulation<-rep(cor$SubPopulation,5)
Type<-rep(cor$type,5)
Name=rep(cor$CellType,5)

phenotype<-c(rep("Gender",nrow(cor)),rep("Age",nrow(cor)),rep("Days_from_Jan_16",nrow(cor)),rep("Seasonal_effect_sin",nrow(cor)),rep("Seasonal_effect_cos",nrow(cor)))

fdr<-as.data.frame(fdr)
fdr_v<-c(fdr$Gender,fdr$Age,fdr$Days_from_Jan_16,fdr$Sin,fdr$Cos)

tmp<-data.frame(Name=Name,correlation_coefficient=cor_value,Subpopulation=Subpopulation,Type=Type,phenotype=phenotype,fdr=fdr_v<0.05)

breaks<-round(seq(-0.7,0.7,0.2),digits = 1)
p=ggplot(data=tmp,aes(phenotype,Name))+geom_tile(aes(fill = correlation_coefficient),colour = "white") + scale_fill_gradient2(low="blue",high = "red",limits=c(-0.7,0.7),breaks=breaks)
p=p+geom_point(data=tmp[tmp$fdr,],aes(phenotype,Name),size=0.2)+facet_grid(Subpopulation~Type,scales = "free", space = "free")
p+theme_bw()+theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90,hjust = 0.5,vjust = 0.5))
